This paper discusses the uptake and usage of OWL in the Linked Data world, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques for reasoning and knowledge representation. It also involves database (DB) management and querying, as well as machine learning (LG) for identifying patterns and making predictions. The paper proposes a new fragment for OWL, which involves software engineering (SE) and system design. Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of this new fragment, which involves systems integration (SI).
